name: Swasthya Swaraj Society
briefDescription: Swasthya Swaraj Society was formed to respond to the crying need for healthcare and the shocking inequity in health existing in the tribal areas  of Kalahandi district in Odisha. The society was formed in March 2014 after a two year period of observations and explorations. It consists mainly of doctors, public health professionals, nurses, paramedics and  other support team. The E.C members now are: (list)Swasthya Swaraj Comprehensive Community Health  Programme is the flagship programme of Swastya Swaraj Society.  It is now operating in 75 tribal dominant villages drawn from 6 gram panchayats of Thuamul Rampur block in Kalahandi district.
